mydotfiles

record contents of some config files in my home directory, like as ".gitconfig",
".bashrc", ".vimrc", etc.

* gitconfig
global config file for git, copy to home directory "~" and rename to ".gitconfig",
edit to change your name and email address.

* vimrc
global config file for vim, copy to home directory "~" and rename to ".vimrc",
please don't forget to backup your origin vimrc file before rename.

* mybashrc
config file for bash, copy to home dirctory "~" and rename to ".bashrc",
please don't forget to backup your origin bashrc file before rename.
recommend to copy as "~/.mybashrc", and include this file in your "~/.bashrc".
